rComments: she was quite possibly the most amicable and direct psych prof at ucsc.... RIP

Prof. White was probably the best teacher I've ever had. She was so entertaining compared to the other two professors. She was always so energetic and showed up with condom earrings. Those of you who haven't had a chance to take her class, have truly missed out.

HANDS DOWN THE BEST TEACHER EVER! I absolutely love the way she teaches. She makes the class entertaining and fun! I recommend anyone who have a chance to take her class, GO FOR IT! She MAKES me enjoy Intro to Psyc. A very good teacher! Study her slides carefully, read, and you will do fine on her midterm! :) I created an account just for this!

A bit of history, anthropology, and social psychology through the lens of ABPsi. A very lenient class, students get to choose their paper topics across a wide variety of research by black psychologists. Great communication throughout, very relaxed. People of all colors and creeds felt welcome and free to share their experiences. Great humor too.

Absolutely amazing professor. She taught the social psychology segment of the course and was VERY clear in her lecture. She is passionate about the subject, and it motivates you to do well. She also attempts to get to know her students, which is nice. She will have you wanting to study and attend lectures regularly. I highly recommend her.

Great professor; she taught the segment on social psych. She gave a lot of examples and showed videos to help students understand the concepts. Also, made a point to only go over what she felt was useful for an introductory psych course and what was going to be on the exam. Very approachable. Took a lot of questions during lectures & office hours.
She is very approachable; its hard to ask questions when the professor is intimidating but she isn't. Great class. I love the way she speaks. Very engaging and inspiring

Dr. White is a great professor. I've had her for African-American Psyc and Peace Psyc. Both were good classes. She is always willing to explain/re-explain concepts. The final paper in each class was challenging but not impossible. She is a bit strict about attendance (5 minutes late=absent) but it's worth it to arrive early to ask questions.
